# Next.js frontend (`src/`)

- **Data**: Use `useQuery`, `useMutation`, `useAction` from **`convex/react`** with generated API from **`convex/_generated/api`**. Pass **`userId`** from Clerk (`useUser`) into Convex calls as required by each function.
- **Layout**: Root layout uses **`ConvexClerkProvider`** and app chrome (**`Sidebar`**). Match existing patterns in **`src/app/layout.tsx`** and **`src/components/`**.
- **UI / UX**: **Teal accent `#0d9488`**, warm neutrals, calm spacing — **not** a cold corporate bank dashboard. Full **`CLAUDE.md` → Design Context** is authoritative for voice, light/dark feel, and anti-patterns (no gradient hero metric cards, etc.).
- **Utilities**: Prefer **`src/lib/utils.ts`** and **`src/lib/icons.ts`** for formatting and icons before adding one-off helpers.
- **Accessibility & responsive**: Mobile-equal experience; touch-friendly controls on small screens.

## Key pages and components

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `app/dashboard/page.tsx` | Main view: full-width expense timeline + category spending section |
| `app/categories/page.tsx` | Budget page: groups → categories with monthly targets and spending |
| `app/accounts/page.tsx` | Bank/cash account management |
| `app/debts/page.tsx` | Loan tracking |
| `app/credit-cards/page.tsx` | Credit card tracking |
| `components/ExpenseTimeline.tsx` | Date-organized timeline; renders debts, credit cards, and categories with due days as `PlannerRow` items |
| `components/CategoryEditModal.tsx` | Reusable modal for creating/editing a category (fetches groups + accounts internally) |
| `components/DebtManager.tsx` | Form for creating/editing a debt; used from Debts page and timeline edit flow |
| `components/TransactionForm.tsx` | Quick-add spending form; payee = category, debt, or credit card |
| `lib/planner.ts` | `PlannerRow` union type that drives the timeline (`budget \| debt \| cc \| category`) |

## Dark mode

All inputs, selects, and textareas use the standard pattern:
```
border-slate-200 dark:border-white/10
text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-100
bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-800 focus:bg-white dark:focus:bg-slate-900
```
Labels: `text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400`. Hint text: `text-slate-400 dark:text-slate-500`. Errors: `text-rose-600 dark:text-rose-400 bg-rose-50 dark:bg-rose-950/40`.
